    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="496"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">661.11241/15a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HLW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 15, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. In connection with representations which have been made to the Soviet
                    Ambassador here with regard to the regime of inspection of personal effects not
                    accompanying departing foreign diplomats as baggage which is imposed by the
                    Soviet authorities, and to the provision for the levying on such effects of
                    export duties or in lieu thereof an appraisal fee, please report by telegraph: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>The names of departing members of the Embassy staff whose effects have
                            been inspected <hi rend="italic">a</hi>) at their dwellings, and <hi
                                rend="italic">b</hi>) at the customs house. Please state dates in
                            each case.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>The names of departing members of the staff who have been requested to
                            pay either an export tax or an appraisal fee, and the <pb facs="0736"
                                n="630" xml:id="pg_630"/> amount of the tax or fee actually paid by
                            them together with the dates on which payment was requested or
                            made.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Such comment as you may wish to make.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
